You can use the Ant [`&lt;compilerarg&gt;`](https://ant.apache.org/manual/Tasks/javac.html) element, which can be nested inside the `&lt;javac&gt;` element. 

Specifically, you need the `javac` [`--enable-preview`](https://docs.oracle.com/en/java/javase/18/language/preview-language-and-vm-features.html) argument.

Example:

```
&lt;target name=&quot;compile&quot; depends=&quot;init&quot; description=&quot;Compile the source.&quot;&gt;
    &lt;javac srcdir=&quot;${src}&quot; classpathref=&quot;classpath&quot; destdir=&quot;${build.bin}&quot; compiler=&quot;modern&quot; debug=&quot;true&quot; debuglevel=&quot;lines,vars,source&quot; includeantruntime=&quot;false&quot; source=&quot;17&quot; target=&quot;17&quot;&gt;
        &lt;compilerarg value=&quot;--enable-preview&quot; /&gt;
    &lt;/javac&gt;
&lt;/target&gt;
```
---

More information and examples for `compilerarg` can be found here: [Ant: passing compilerarg into javac](https://stackoverflow.com/q/4134803/12567365)

